  estimate 100
      desc 'perl--HTML-Mason is a Perl-based web site development and delivery system
that allows web pages and sites to be constructed from
shared, reusable building blocks called components.
Components contain a mix of Perl and HTML, and can call
each other and pass values back and forth like subroutines.
Components increase modularity and eliminate repetitive work:
common design elements (headers, footers, menus, logos) can
be extracted into their own components where they
need be changed only once to affect the whole site.
Other Mason features include powerful filtering and templating
facilities, and a HTML/data caching model.
See http://www.masonhq.com/ for more information.
